{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"8ed0e039-6f3a-4cf3-bb8a-a31aba9c1738","content":"No files found in the working directory. I'll show you exactly how to convert and catch errors at build time.\n\n## 1. Add `x:DataType` to your XAML\n\nOn the root `ContentPage` element, add the `x:DataType` attribute pointing to your ViewModel:\n\n```xml\n<ContentPage xmlns=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui\"\n             xmlns:x=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml\"\n             xmlns:vm=\"clr-namespace:YourApp.ViewModels\"\n             x:Class=\"YourApp.Views.SettingsPage\"\n             x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\">\n\n    <VerticalStackLayout Padding=\"20\" Spacing=\"15\">\n\n        <Label Text=\"{Binding Theme}\" FontSize=\"{Binding FontSize}\" />\n\n        <Switch IsToggled=\"{Binding NotificationsEnabled}\" />\n\n        <Slider Minimum=\"10\" Maximum=\"30\"\n                Value=\"{Binding FontSize}\" />\n\n    </VerticalStackLayout>\n</ContentPage>\n```\n\nThat single `x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\"` attribute is the key change. The XAML compiler now resolves every `{Binding …}` against the declared type at **compile time** instead of using runtime reflection.\n\n## 2. Catch binding errors at build time\n\nCompiled bindings already emit **build errors** (not just warnings) when a property name is wrong. To make sure you get the full benefit:\n\n**a) Enable `$(MauiStrictXamlCompilation)` in your `.csproj`:**\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n    <MauiStrictXamlCompilation>true</MauiStrictXamlCompilation>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\nThis promotes any remaining XAML binding issues to errors.\n\n**b) Treat warnings as errors (optional but recommended):**\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n    <WarningsAsErrors>XC0045;XC0022</WarningsAsErrors>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n- `XC0045` — binding path not found on the declared type  \n- `XC0022` — missing `x:DataType` on a binding expression  \n\nNow if you typo a property (e.g. `{Binding Thme}`), the build fails immediately instead of silently producing a blank label at runtime.\n\n## Quick checklist\n\n| Item | What to do |\n|---|---|\n| `x:DataType` on root | Points to ViewModel type |\n| `xmlns:vm` namespace | Must match ViewModel's CLR namespace |\n| Nested `DataTemplate` | Add its own `x:DataType` for the item type |\n| Need to opt out locally | Use `x:DataType=\"x:Null\"` on that element |\n| `.csproj` strict mode | `<MauiStrictXamlCompilation>true</MauiStrictXamlCompilation>` |","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"3cc49e5f-d5ff-4ddc-a6e2-b04a7db8e407","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"There are no files in the working directory. The user is asking me to help them convert a page they have, but they haven't provided the actual files. I should provide guidance on how to convert a MAUI ContentPage to use compiled bindings with `x:DataType`.\n\nLet me give them a clear, concise answer with before/after examples and explain how to catch binding errors at build time.","outputTokens":811,"requestId":"F404:2EB5E6:1F51C69:2319D2B:69E81961"},"id":"256c6813-5b28-4f26-9bcd-1a361fa12595","timestamp":"2026-04-22T00:42:24.989Z","parentId":"29c19242-3ce5-4d76-ab6e-0d871e873e6c"}
